%N A394500 Ways to represent n = k + p where p is prime and k > 0 is not squarefree.
%H A394500 Ethan S. Lee and Rowan O'Clarey, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.02426">On the Sum of a Prime and a Number that is not Square-Free</a>, arXiv preprint (2026). arXiv:2605.02426 [math.NT]
%F A394500 Lee & O'Clarey prove that a(n) > 0 for large enough n and conjecture that a(n) > 0 for n > 24.
%o A394500 (PARI) a(n)=my(s); forfactored(k=4,n-2, if(issquarefree(k), next); if(isprime(n-k[1]), s++)); s \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, May 24 2026
